Next time you go shopping...please remember that yes we are paid to do the work, but we can provide you much better service if you do your part too.<br>
Check for signs stating how many items you are allowed to take in to the fitting rooms...and follow the rules.  If you have more items to try on than you are allowed to take, and you don't have a second person there to help you...ask the nearest cashier if there is somewhere you can put the extras.  We can't police every customer, and some managers will chew the cashier out even on the busiest day of the year.<br>
At the very least, don't leave the items you don't want just piled all over the floor, hangers everywhere, inside out and tangled up.  If you can't be bothered to walk them out to the rack designated for excess merchandise, or back to where you got them....at least hang the things back up.  I spend more time cleaning out fitting rooms and untangling clothes than out on the floor helping customers because of this.<br>
Don't blame me if I can't do something exactly the way you want.  All places have these things called policies that have to be followed....just because you're shopping not working doesn't mean that the rules are going to be rewritten for you.  I'll be more than happy to do the most I can for you, but I can't change the rules.<br>
Finally....I don't care how bad your day has been, you have no right to get in my face and yell and curse at me when things are not going your way.  9 times out of 10 I am working with my back aching, my feet feeling like they are falling off, and a splitting migraine headache, yet I keep a smile on my face, a cheerful greeting for you, and go out of my way to try and make your shopping experience more pleasant.  The last thing I need to add onto that is resenting what I do.<br>
<br>
Anywho.../rant off. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
